What's going on is again fairly
straightforward and simple.

00:57:44.840 --> 00:57:52.237
That it was this slide that I
want--here is again fairly

00:57:52.237 --> 00:57:54.119
recent data.
 

00:57:54.119 --> 00:57:58.072
Chinese women interviewed in
1981, but referring to their

00:57:58.072 --> 00:58:02.166
pregnancies which had been
sometime in the past and it says

00:58:02.166 --> 00:58:06.472
it tried to gather data on what
was the birth interval of your

00:58:06.472 --> 00:58:09.650
children and how many of them
survived?

00:58:09.650 --> 00:58:13.918
If the birth interval was less
than two years 45% of the

00:58:13.918 --> 00:58:15.159
children died.
 

00:58:15.159 --> 00:58:20.780
If it was between two and three
years, 34% of the children died.

00:58:20.780 --> 00:58:26.335
If it was more than three
years, only 19% of the children

00:58:26.335 --> 00:58:27.030
died.
 

00:58:27.030 --> 00:58:31.164
In every culture and every time
and place where we have data

00:58:31.164 --> 00:58:35.228
like this it's very clear that
if the birth interval is too

00:58:35.228 --> 00:58:38.820
small,
the children just don't survive.

00:58:38.820 --> 00:58:44.393
What's going on with pushing
down the fertility rate is that

00:58:44.393 --> 00:58:46.507
it--
especially in situations of

00:58:46.507 --> 00:58:48.800
poverty where resources are not
great,

00:58:48.800 --> 00:58:51.440
women are not especially
healthy, there's no--

00:58:51.440 --> 00:58:56.032
any kind of medicine available,
that if the child does not get

00:58:56.032 --> 00:58:59.311
a lot of resources,
which a large case is milk from

00:58:59.311 --> 00:59:01.090
the mother is the primary
thing--

00:59:01.090 --> 00:59:05.887
in China there's no dairy
products at this time in this

00:59:05.887 --> 00:59:07.219
social class.
 

00:59:07.219 --> 00:59:09.880
It's largely food directly from
the mother;

00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:12.570
the children are just going to
die.

00:59:12.570 --> 00:59:17.119
The reason that fertility is
pushed up from below,

00:59:17.119 --> 00:59:22.876
is pushed down is not to reduce
total number of children but to

00:59:22.876 --> 00:59:25.940
maximize surviving fertility.
 

00:59:25.940 --> 00:59:28.547
What people aim is not to just
keep popping them out and having

00:59:28.547 --> 00:59:29.010
them die.
 

00:59:29.010 --> 00:59:33.952
What people aim at and cultures
have learned to accommodate to

00:59:33.952 --> 00:59:36.949
is to maximize surviving
fertility.

00:59:36.949 --> 00:59:39.929
Not total fertility,
which is just being born,

00:59:39.929 --> 00:59:44.440
but maximizing the number of
children that are going to stay

00:59:44.440 --> 00:59:48.032
alive to become adult
reproducing members of the

00:59:48.032 --> 00:59:48.949
society.
 

00:59:48.949 --> 00:59:55.639
Now people have many mechanisms
for limiting the birth rate.

00:59:55.639 --> 01:00:00.880
One that is often quite
conscious is breastfeeding;

01:00:00.880 --> 01:00:03.960
it's a very standard method
across many cultures.

01:00:03.960 --> 01:00:08.320
You've all heard of this,
lactation amenorrhea,

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:14.300
and many, many cultures don't
leave--

01:00:14.300 --> 01:00:16.563
I mean in our culture a woman
can breastfeed a little bit or

01:00:16.563 --> 01:00:18.157
long,
it's totally up to the

01:00:18.157 --> 01:00:18.860
individual.
 

01:00:18.860 --> 01:00:22.989
Many cultures are very strict
rules about this.

01:00:22.989 --> 01:00:26.070
You must breastfeed for at
least--and there's a certain

01:00:26.070 --> 01:00:27.039
period of time.
 

01:00:27.039 --> 01:00:31.702
Among the !Kung of Southwest
Africa, which these people speak

01:00:31.702 --> 01:00:35.510
this click language,
they've got all these--you've

01:00:35.510 --> 01:00:36.909
heard of them.
 

01:00:36.909 --> 01:00:39.849
Mothers keep the infant with
them at all times,

01:00:39.849 --> 01:00:42.981
they nurse all day,
at intervals separated by only

01:00:42.981 --> 01:00:43.940
15 minutes.
 

01:00:43.940 --> 01:00:46.869
Bonnie how would you like to
have that all day long?

01:00:46.869 --> 01:00:49.639
Nurse every 15 minutes the
child;

01:00:49.639 --> 01:00:53.211
they sleep next to the mother,
and have access to her breast

01:00:53.211 --> 01:00:56.722
all night long and the nursing
continues until the child is

01:00:56.722 --> 01:00:58.539
more than three years old.
 

01:00:58.539 --> 01:01:02.050
By that mechanism,
primarily by the lactation

01:01:02.050 --> 01:01:06.918
amenorrhea, the birth interval
among !Kung is four years which

01:01:06.918 --> 01:01:10.110
fits--is beyond this survival
issue.

01:01:10.110 --> 01:01:15.659
This is the kind of--I talked
about Nomads and people that

01:01:15.659 --> 01:01:19.025
have--
fairly conscious--they're

01:01:19.025 --> 01:01:25.130
probably are aware that this is
limiting the births and it's

01:01:25.130 --> 01:01:28.650
something that they want to do.
 

01:01:28.650 --> 01:01:33.210
When the women go foraging they
carry their children--

01:01:33.210 --> 01:01:35.969
again the !Kung,
they carry their children with

01:01:35.969 --> 01:01:39.570
them until their four years old
and while carrying the infant

01:01:39.570 --> 01:01:42.210
she walks up to 12 miles round
trip to--

01:01:42.210 --> 01:01:46.280
it takes 6 miles to go out and
find some food and come back;

01:01:46.280 --> 01:01:50.059
12 miles round trip and then in
addition to that she carries

01:01:50.059 --> 01:01:51.789
loads of 15 to 35 pounds.
 

01:01:51.789 --> 01:01:55.465
Here's a woman who--being a
hunter gatherer is probably

01:01:55.465 --> 01:01:59.177
fairly healthy,
she's carrying an infant on her

01:01:59.177 --> 01:02:02.110
back,
walking around 12 miles,

01:02:02.110 --> 01:02:07.050
and coming back with a load of
35 pounds of food.

01:02:07.050 --> 01:02:10.570
It's quite a feat and it's
clear that they can't--

01:02:10.570 --> 01:02:12.260
they're not going to have a
second infant,

01:02:12.260 --> 01:02:14.789
one on the back,
one of the hip,

01:02:14.789 --> 01:02:18.219
this is not a way of improving
survival.

01:02:18.219 --> 01:02:22.530
That's--lactation is one
mechanism.

01:02:22.530 --> 01:02:28.557
There's many taboos on sexual
relations, especially after

01:02:28.557 --> 01:02:29.420
birth.
 

01:02:29.420 --> 01:02:32.271
In many cultures,
as I said, a prescribed period

01:02:32.271 --> 01:02:33.059
of nursing.
 

01:02:33.059 --> 01:02:37.317
There's also a post-partum
taboo against having sexual

01:02:37.317 --> 01:02:41.333
relations, and again,
another obvious mechanism for

01:02:41.333 --> 01:02:42.780
birth spacing.
 

01:02:42.780 --> 01:02:48.092
If you--again this gets to the
degree of consciousness of these

01:02:48.092 --> 01:02:48.949
methods.
 

01:02:48.949 --> 01:02:52.610
If you ask a member of a
society that has a taboo they

01:02:52.610 --> 01:02:56.686
report for instance that sex at
that time is very dangerous,

01:02:56.686 --> 01:02:58.619
a life and death matter.
 

01:02:58.619 --> 01:03:01.820
It is dangerous to mix the
man's blood with the woman's,

01:03:01.820 --> 01:03:04.789
and the man's blood is
transmitted through semen.

01:03:04.789 --> 01:03:08.088
It's a bodily fluid and they
don't totally--the biology is

01:03:08.088 --> 01:03:09.130
not very strong.
 

01:03:09.130 --> 01:03:12.731
Their course at Yale was
terrible--we'll talk a lot

01:03:12.731 --> 01:03:14.844
about--
not a lot--some,

01:03:14.844 --> 01:03:19.331
about what pre--pre-education
people believe about

01:03:19.331 --> 01:03:22.170
reproduction and everything.
 

01:03:22.170 --> 01:03:28.509
If man's blood gets into the
woman through his semen then it

01:03:28.509 --> 01:03:33.166
also gets into her milk,
and then the man's blood goes

01:03:33.166 --> 01:03:36.920
back into the baby through the
mother's milk and this is poison

01:03:36.920 --> 01:03:37.889
for the baby.
 

01:03:37.889 --> 01:03:43.960
That's their version of why
they shouldn't--why they have

01:03:43.960 --> 01:03:45.369
this taboo.
 

01:03:45.369 --> 01:03:47.320
We see this in the evolution of
cultures,

01:03:47.320 --> 01:03:49.099
I mean just as we evolve
biologically,

01:03:49.099 --> 01:03:52.869
of course evolve culturally,
that cultures may--

01:03:52.869 --> 01:03:56.766
will pick up a behavioral
pattern for who knows what

01:03:56.766 --> 01:03:59.172
reason,
and they may have no clue what

01:03:59.172 --> 01:04:01.916
it's 'real' as we see it,
it's 'real' purpose is,

01:04:01.916 --> 01:04:05.003
in this case to space births
apart they have some kind of

01:04:05.003 --> 01:04:08.143
cultural story about it and it
doesn't matter whether that

01:04:08.143 --> 01:04:10.679
cultural story has any degree of
reality.

01:04:10.679 --> 01:04:13.635
If they've picked up a cultural
norm that works,

01:04:13.635 --> 01:04:16.969
the society is still here,
and that gets passed on.

01:04:16.969 --> 01:04:22.775
If that cultural practice does
not work, not only reproduction,

01:04:22.775 --> 01:04:26.710
all sorts of ways,
that society is gone.

01:04:26.710 --> 01:04:31.760
This post-partum abstinence is
a major issue,

01:04:31.760 --> 01:04:34.860
especially in Africa now.
 

01:04:34.860 --> 01:04:40.170
The abstinence is up to three
years which is--that's sort of

01:04:40.170 --> 01:04:42.780
the mode of this in Africa.
 

01:04:42.780 --> 01:04:46.889
In addition to limit births,
there's another thing which

01:04:46.889 --> 01:04:50.030
again is a population limitation
issue,

01:04:50.030 --> 01:04:52.097
because we've talked about
individual family limitation

01:04:52.097 --> 01:04:53.900
issues,
trying to keep the kid alive.

01:04:53.900 --> 01:04:58.186
If the village is resource
limited they may have mechanisms

01:04:58.186 --> 01:05:02.768
for keeping the whole population
of the whole village down,

01:05:02.768 --> 01:05:06.099
and so in Africa especially,
they have a thing called

01:05:06.099 --> 01:05:07.510
terminal abstinence.
 

01:05:07.510 --> 01:05:10.782
That means at a certain point
in life the culture demands that

01:05:10.782 --> 01:05:12.659
you stop having sexual
relations.

01:05:12.659 --> 01:05:16.710
Very often this is when your
daughter has her first child.

01:05:16.710 --> 01:05:19.699
After that you're a
grandmother, and you're not

01:05:19.699 --> 01:05:21.780
supposed to reproduce anymore.
 

01:05:21.780 --> 01:05:25.110
It's interesting what--to
prevent--they perceive it as

01:05:25.110 --> 01:05:28.882
preventing conflicts between
their duties as mother and their

01:05:28.882 --> 01:05:31.891
duties as grandmother,
so a grandmother is supposed to

01:05:31.891 --> 01:05:33.159
help raise the grandchildren.
 

01:05:33.159 --> 01:05:36.909
And there's a lot of biological
theory about why do humans,

01:05:36.909 --> 01:05:41.820
somewhat unique among animals,
why don't we just die --

01:05:41.820 --> 01:05:43.550
females especially after their
fertile period,

01:05:43.550 --> 01:05:45.929
there's no reason for you to
evolutionarily stay alive,

01:05:45.929 --> 01:05:49.980
most animals they don't have a
post-menopausal period.

01:05:49.980 --> 01:05:53.929
The theoretical reason is the
grandmother effect,

01:05:53.929 --> 01:05:57.956
that as a grandmother you
support the children of your

01:05:57.956 --> 01:06:00.369
child,
and that increases their

01:06:00.369 --> 01:06:03.469
survival, and so it's
evolutionarily good.

01:06:03.469 --> 01:06:05.646
Here in these tribes in Africa,
are basically saying the same

01:06:05.646 --> 01:06:07.605
thing that if you're a
grandmother you're going to have

01:06:07.605 --> 01:06:09.818
a conflict between taking care
of your own children and taking

01:06:09.818 --> 01:06:11.268
care of your daughter's
children,

01:06:11.268 --> 01:06:16.659
and that conflict is bad so you
have to not engage in sexuality.

01:06:16.659 --> 01:06:19.909
Up to the middle of the 1900s
in Ireland,

01:06:19.909 --> 01:06:22.755
rural Ireland,
people lived in households with

01:06:22.755 --> 01:06:26.170
many members of both sexes and
several generations,

01:06:26.170 --> 01:06:28.530
big multi-family houses.
 

01:06:28.530 --> 01:06:31.757
The Irish believe that there
should be only one sexually

01:06:31.757 --> 01:06:35.514
active procreative couple in the
household, so they also practice

01:06:35.514 --> 01:06:37.099
grandmother abstinence.
 

01:06:37.099 --> 01:06:41.527
These cultural items are--they
may seem a little outlandish to

01:06:41.527 --> 01:06:44.940
us in our modern day but they
were effective.

01:06:44.940 --> 01:06:52.510
They kept that society going.
 

01:06:52.510 --> 01:06:57.719
Another issue is exogamy,
that just like chimpanzees,

01:06:57.719 --> 01:07:01.900
it's again in most animals,
it's the males that disperse,

01:07:01.900 --> 01:07:06.010
but in chimps and humans it's
the females that disperse.

01:07:06.010 --> 01:07:10.079
The females leave the community
at birth,

01:07:10.079 --> 01:07:13.697
to go live with the man's
family, and so she's under the

01:07:13.697 --> 01:07:17.159
control then,
in many cultures basically a

01:07:17.159 --> 01:07:22.266
slave to the son's family,
and the reproductive rules are

01:07:22.266 --> 01:07:27.751
then set by the son's family and
she has no choice in this and

01:07:27.751 --> 01:07:32.358
we'll talk about that extra--
this out marrying--remember

01:07:32.358 --> 01:07:36.010
with chimpanzees they were
hostile to the neighbors around

01:07:36.010 --> 01:07:38.643
us,
human societies are that same

01:07:38.643 --> 01:07:39.018
way.
 

01:07:39.018 --> 01:07:44.590
The professor in the lab next
to me is from China,

01:07:44.590 --> 01:07:47.777
a village near Shanghai,
and he describes this to me in

01:07:47.777 --> 01:07:49.331
China,
and he says my village,

01:07:49.331 --> 01:07:51.018
which have all the same name as
him,

01:07:51.018 --> 01:07:54.355
it's all a male bonded,
the males have been there

01:07:54.355 --> 01:07:56.554
forever,
they all have the same last

01:07:56.554 --> 01:07:59.746
name--they're hostile to all the
villages around them so they

01:07:59.746 --> 01:08:01.820
won't marry the village around
them.

01:08:01.820 --> 01:08:06.148
To get married they have to go
two villages away and they're

01:08:06.148 --> 01:08:07.909
still sort of enemies.
 

01:08:07.909 --> 01:08:10.409
In New Guinea where all over
the world that's the same

01:08:10.409 --> 01:08:11.929
problem,
you're fighting with your

01:08:11.929 --> 01:08:13.695
neighbors,
and yet you have to get wives

01:08:13.695 --> 01:08:16.912
from somewhere,
you have to exchange genetic

01:08:16.912 --> 01:08:20.271
material,
otherwise you get inbreeding

01:08:20.271 --> 01:08:25.313
and so the Mae Enga they say in
New Guinea that we marry our

01:08:25.313 --> 01:08:27.659
enemies and--
this is a great story.

01:08:27.659 --> 01:08:30.747
Time is up;
I will continue this story next

01:08:30.747 --> 01:08:31.220
time.
 

